│ The patch adds conservative guards to SimplifyIndVar to prevent unsound       │
│ constant folding of IV comparisons when ScalarEvolution expressions may       │
│ involve undefined behavior like udiv by zero.                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ Key changes:                                                                  │
│ - In eliminateIVComparison, before attempting to evaluate the predicate to a  │
│ constant, we now:                                                             │
│   - Bail out on equality/inequality predicates, which are particularly prone  │
│ to issues in presence of poison.                                              │
│   - Bail out if the loop contains an explicit udiv-by-zero instruction.       │
│   - Bail out if either SCEV operand contains undef values or involves udiv    │
│ expressions, especially with zero divisors. For this, we added a helper       │
│ containsPoisonousUDiv to recursively detect SCEVUDivExpr with zero RHS.       │
│ - Similar early return added in makeIVComparisonInvariant for EQ/NE           │
│ predicates.                                                                   │
│ - Introduced helpers containsPoisonousUDiv and loopHasUDivByZero to           │
│ conservatively detect problematic cases.                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ This prevents indvars from replacing the %phi == 0 comparison with a constant │
│ in the provided reproducer, avoiding the incorrect transformation path.       │
